\ltrch and {\highlight7 @hh}{\highlight7 <HEB>}\rtlch \'ee\'c8\'e7\'c3\'ec\'c8\'ef{\highlight7 {\ltrch @ee}}{\highlight7 {\ltrch<}{\ltrch ENG}{\ltrch>}}\ltrch  at all times. He is thus intrinsically a Pardoner and Forgiver.— Pesher Dovor\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <*58>}58{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}The literal meaning of {\highlight7 @hh}{\highlight7 <HEB>}\rtlch \'e7\'c7\'e3\'c0\'f8\'c5\'e9 \'e1\'c8\'e8\'c6\'ef{\highlight7 {\ltrch @ee}}{\highlight7 {\ltrch<}{\ltrch ENG}{\ltrch>}}\ltrch  is “chambers of the stomach,” but according to Ibn Ezra to 
