{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <*53>}53{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}This refers to idle talk and gossip.\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <*54>}54{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}This includes profanity and unclean language.\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <*55>}55{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}When a person allows his Evil Inclination to rule over him, he commits a sin.\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <*56>}56{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}We ask Hashem to pardon us even for sins we are not aware that we committed, and also 
