{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <*68>}68{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}Mishnah Yoma ch. 1:6. Since it was necessary that he not fall asleep lest he have an impure 
emission while sleeping, those around him kept him up all night.\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <*69>}69{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}Ibid. For at midnight, the service of Yom Kippur begins with the Terumas HaDeshen, which 
