{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <*86>}86{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}It was incumbent upon him to wash before taking off his clothes and then once again after 
putting on new ones.\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <*87>}87{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}Mishnah Yoma 3:8. The High Priest would sacrifice two oxen on Yom Kippur. One he 
brought for himself, from his own funds, and one for the Jewish people, from public funds.\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <*88>}88{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}The ox stood in the northern sector of the area between the outer Altar and the Sanctuary. It 
